{
  "texts": [
    "Li et al. (2023) review model fusion across architectures and disjoint training runs.",
    "Yang et al. (2024a) group LLM merging approaches into \"Pre-Merging Methods\" (weight alignment), \"During-Merging Methods\" (weight combination), and \"Theories and Analysis\".",
    "We use \"merging methods\" to denote the second category.",
    "Ruan et al. (2025) classify merging approaches with emphasis on pruning, while Yadav et al. (2024) systematically study merging across model scales up to 64B parameters.",
    "Our work complements these analyses by incorporating additional recent subspace methods and evaluating widely used open-weight models (Qwen3 and Llama 3) rather than proprietary PaLM models."
  ]
}